## Argument Reference

* `template_name` ‚Äî (Required, String) Identifier for the template, used as the URL key
  for updates and deletes. Changing this forces a new resource.
* `resource_id` ‚Äî (Optional, String) ID of the
  `orcasecurity_integration_servicenow_resource` resource that carries the credentials.
* `instance_name` ‚Äî (Optional, String) ServiceNow instance subdomain (for example,
  `ven03666`). Mutually exclusive with `base_url`. Required when no `resource_id` is
  given.
* `base_url` ‚Äî (Optional, String) Full ServiceNow base URL (`https://...`). Mutually
  exclusive with `instance_name`. Takes precedence over `instance_name` if both are
  set.
* `username` ‚Äî (Optional, String) ServiceNow username override. Usually inherited
  from the linked resource.
* `resolution_status` ‚Äî (Optional, String) ServiceNow incident state code to use
  when Orca resolves a ticket.
* `resolution_code` ‚Äî (Optional, String) ServiceNow close code.
* `resolution_note` ‚Äî (Optional, String) ServiceNow close notes.
* `reopen_status` ‚Äî (Optional, String) Incident state code Orca moves a ticket to
  when re-opening it.
* `mapping_json` ‚Äî (Optional, String) JSON-encoded `mapping` object. Each key is a
  ServiceNow field name and the value is a list of `{ "orca": "<alert_field>" }`
  (pull a value from the Orca alert) or `{ "value": "<literal>" }` (a static
  value). Use `jsonencode({...})` to keep the HCL readable.
* `on_close_alert_mapping_json` ‚Äî (Optional, String) JSON-encoded
  `on_close_alert_mapping` object used when an Orca-driven close event syncs back
  to ServiceNow.
* `allow_reopen_and_resolution` ‚Äî (Optional, Bool) Default `false`.
* `allow_mapping` ‚Äî (Optional, Bool) Default `false`.
* `is_enabled` ‚Äî (Optional, Bool) Default `true`.
* `is_default` ‚Äî (Optional, Bool) Default `false`.

> **Note:** Orca does not accept `business_units` on this endpoint ‚Äî the UI
> does not send it either. To scope a template to specific business units,
> manage the scoping at the credentials resource (`orcasecurity_integration_servicenow_resource`)
> level or via Orca's RBAC.

## Attribute Reference

* `id` ‚Äî (String) Orca external service config identifier (UUID).

